com.nokia.maps.component.touch

Class TouchEventHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nokia.maps.component.touch.TouchEventHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExtendedEventListener, EventListener

    public class TouchEventHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements ExtendedEventListener
    This class provides a framework for handling touch and gesture events. Gesture events are only handled if components are placed on a GestureMapCanvas, events are passed to the associated MapComponent if and only if the specified hit area has been touched.
    See Also:
    TouchComponent

        public boolean pointerReleased(int x,

        Specified by:
        pointerReleased in interface EventListener

        Returns:
        true if pointer event was consumed, false otherwise.

      • flick

        public boolean flick(int x,
            int y,
            float direction,
            int speed,
            int speedX,
            int speedY)
        This method is called from the GestureMapCanvas when a Flick has occurred. . The event is passed on to the associated MapComponent if the flick occurred within its hit area. Note the MapComponent must be placed on a GestureMapCanvas and the device must support the Gesture API to respond to the flick() event.
        Specified by:
        flick in interface ExtendedEventListener
        Parameters:
        x - x axis pixel coordinate on the screen where the flick event occurred.
        y - y axis pixel coordinate on the screen where the flick event occurred.
        direction - direction of the flick event.
        speed - speed of the flick.
        speedX - speed of the flick on the x axis.
        speedY - speed of the flick on the y axis.
        Returns:
        true if the event should be consumed or false if it should be passed to subsequent event handlers.

      • pinch

        public boolean pinch(int x,
            int y,
            int centerX,
            int centerY,
            int centerChangeX,
            int centerChangeY,
            int distanceStarting,
            int distanceCurrent,
            int distanceChange)
        This method is called from the GestureMapCanvas when a Pinch has occurred. . The event is passed on to the associated MapComponent if the pinch occurred within its hit area. Note the MapComponent must be placed on a GestureMapCanvas and the device must support the Gesture API to respond to the pinch() event.
        Specified by:
        pinch in interface ExtendedEventListener
        Parameters:
        x - x axis pixel coordinate on the screen where the pinch started.
        y - y axis pixel coordinate on the screen where the pinch started.
        centerX - x axis pixel coordinate describing the current centre of the pinch
        centerY - y axis pixel coordinate describing the current centre of the pinch.
        centerChangeX - difference in x axis pixel coordinate from initial to current location
        centerChangeY - difference in y axis pixel coordinate from intiial to current location
        distanceStarting - initial number of pixels between the pinch points
        distanceCurrent - current number of pixels between the pinch points
        distanceChange - difference in size between the original can current pinch sizes.
        Returns:
        true if the event should be consumed or false if it should be passed to subsequent event handlers.
